swarm
------------------------------------------
The purpose of swarm is to provide a novel clustering algorithm that handles
massive sets of amplicons. Results of traditional clustering algorithms are
strongly input-order dependent, and rely on an arbitrary global clustering
threshold. swarm results are resilient to input-order changes and rely on a
small local linking threshold d, representing the maximum number of differences
between two amplicons. swarm forms stable, high-resolution clusters, with a
high yield of biological information.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/torognes/swarm

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/torognes/swarm/archive/refs/tags/v3.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack swarm-3.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./swarm-3.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/swarm-3.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/swarm-3.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(swarm)
  /usr/bin/swarm.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/swarm.README
  /usr/share/doc/swarm/CITATION
  /usr/share/doc/swarm/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/swarm/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/swarm/swarm_manual.pdf
  /usr/share/man/man1/swarm.1.gz

